<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALLONE SCORED A HIT WITH HIS COURAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for the story on former major league umpire Dave Pallone, who has 
written a book about his life in baseball as a closeted gay man. 
</P>
<P>
Pallone's story dramatizes the pain all of us who are lesbian and gay 
experience when we are forced to hide our identities to avoid discrimination 
and bigotry. 
</P>
<P>
Professional baseball, like other American institutions, needs to wake up to 
the fact that lesbians and gay men are active in all walks of life, including 
major league sports. 
</P>
<P>
A person's sexual orientation is an integral part of who that person is, and 
discrimination based on that orientation is just as immoral as racism and other 
forms of bigotry. For people like Pallone to have to hide a basic part of their 
identity to do the work they love is a tragedy, benefiting no one. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD JENNINGS 
</P>
<P>
Co-President, Gay &amp; Lesbian Alliance Against Defamation/L.A. 
