<HEADLINE>
<P>
AID FOR QUAKE VICTIMS IN IRAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Every blanket, every gauze bandage, every can of provisions that the government 
of Iran accepts from the United States, England and the other countries Iranian 
officials condemn (and terrorize) as agents of the Great Satan should be 
imprinted not with the traditional Red Cross but with two other words: Salman 
Rushdie. 
</P>
<P>
ROWENA MALTESE 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
