<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BAKER; 
</P>
<P>
ACID SPILL CLOSES INTERSTATE 15 LANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A hydrochloric acid spill on Interstate 15 near Baker closed several lanes of 
the highway from Los Angeles to Las Vegas for hours as road crews worked to 
remove the caustic chemical, authorities said Saturday. California Highway 
Patrol officials said the driver of a tank truck carrying the chemical found a 
crack in the tank when he stopped to check his brakes a mile north of the 
Halloran Springs exit and 11 miles north of Baker. 
</P>
<P>
About 600 gallons of acid leaked, authorities said. Road crews were draining 
the rest of the acidic cargo onto dirt beside the road and planned to transfer 
the dirt to another tank truck. In the interim, CHP officials advised travelers 
to take Interstate 40 east from Barstow to U.S. 95, north to the Nevada state 
line and then into Las Vegas. 
</P>
