<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
CALTRANS BEGINS HIGHWAY REPAVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
State transportation officials are asking commuters who use California 118 
between Simi Valley and Moorpark to be patient the next several weeks as 
workers repave a section of the road. 
</P>
<P>
The $400,000 improvement project, which began last week, covers a half-mile 
section between Alamos Canyon Road and the Simi Valley Landfill, Caltrans 
engineer Robert Joe said. 
</P>
<P>
Moisture in the soil under the roadway has caused the pavement to bow and 
crack, Joe said. 
</P>
<P>
Only one lane of the four-lane highway will be closed at a time during the 
construction period, Joe said. The work is scheduled to be completed by Aug. 
24. CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
