<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARSONIST STRIKES AGAIN AT LANCASTER SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second time in a week, a fire was set Saturday afternoon at a Lancaster 
junior high school, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
An arsonist set a fire at the Parkview Middle School at the corner of Avenue J 
and Fig Avenue, Lt. Dan Reidder of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The blaze, to which firefighters were sent at 4:50 p.m., caused $150,000 in 
property damage. No people were in the school during the fire and nobody was 
injured, Reidder said. 
</P>
<P>
An arsonist set fire to the Monte Vista Junior High School in Lancaster July 
23. Police are investigating the possibility that the same person set the two 
fires, Reidder said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
