<HEADLINE>
<P>
DONALD TRUMP'S WOES ARE NO LAUGHING MATTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allan Sloan seems to think that it is fun to watch a man go down the tubes. His 
immature delight over Donald J. Trump's financial problems only sheds light to 
me of the columnist's sadism and the fact that he probably should be writing 
for one of the scandal tabloids. 
</P>
<P>
The reporting of information was as shallow as his attitude, and it is 
fortunate that he was not writing an article on AIDS. 
</P>
<P>
While he was rolling in the aisles he forgot to let us know about the effects 
of the Trump default on bondholders and the shareholders, the market, the 
economy in the areas of Trump holdings, the position the lawyers involved in 
the Trump divorce are now taking and probably a multitude of other 
ramifications that a good reporter would look into in a situation like this. 
</P>
<P>
I am sure your readers, including this one, would not delight in the fact that 
Mr. Sloan lost his job even though we would rather read about business in the 
Business section. 
</P>
<P>
ALLAN DORFMAN 
</P>
<P>
Del Mar 
</P>
</TEXT>
