<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROFIT KEY WINS DWYER STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Profit Key took the lead at the start and maintained his advantage throughout 
Saturday to win the 73rd running of the $171,600 Grade II Dwyer Stakes for 
3-year-olds at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
Rhythm, ridden by Craig Perret, raced wide through the stretch to finish second 
in the four-horse field, 1 3/4 lengths ahead of Graf. 
</P>
<P>
The winner, with Jose Santos aboard, carried the co-highweight of 123. 
</P>
<P>
For Profit Key, a Kentucky bred son of Desert Wine-Sharm a Sheikh, the win was 
the second in a row and the fifth in seven starts this year. He covered 1 1/8 
miles in 1:47 2/5 to earn $102,960 and return $3.20 and $2.10. 
</P>
<P>
Rhythm, who had won two in a row, including Belmont's Colin Stakes in his last 
start, paid $2.10. There was no show betting. 
</P>
