<P>
VALLEY'S CLARKE FINISHES STRONGLY TO WIN HEPTATHLON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Valley College's Melanie Clarke turned in a torrid second-day performance to 
post a come-from-behind victory in the heptathlon in The Athletics Congress 
junior championships in Fresno. 
</P>
<P>
Clarke totaled 5,080 points to outdistance Edwina Ammonds (4,958) of Kings 
River College, Kalleen Madden (4,931) of Texas A &amp; M, and pre-meet favorite 
Tish Milligan (4,821) of the Knoxville Track Club. 
</P>
<P>
Third after the first four events Thursday with 3,026 points, Clarke maintained 
that position with a mark of 17 feet 9 1/4 inches in the long jump to start 
Friday's final three events, then took the lead for good with a personal-best 
121-1 in the javelin. 
</P>
<P>
She capped the day with a time of 2 minutes 24.11 seconds in the 800. Clarke's 
marks in the javelin and the 800 were the best in the 14-woman field. 
</P>
<P>
Although Clarke won, she fell short of the qualifying standard (5,300 points) 
for the World Junior Championships in Plovdiv, Bulgaria, Aug. 8-12. 
</P>
