<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAN LEAVING CONCERT HIT BY CAR, KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man walking down the middle of a traffic lane on Irvine Center Drive was 
struck from behind and killed Friday night in concert traffic departing nearby 
Irvine Meadows Amphitheatre. 
</P>
<P>
Police identified the dead man as Michael Rubio, 19, of Sylmar. Officers said 
he was struck by a car driven by Patricia Maureen Feldt, 18, of Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
Police said it did not appear that Feldt had been speeding. They said that 
"alcohol may be a factor" in the accident but provided no details. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
PEDESTRIANS; TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; ACCIDENTAL DEATHS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
