<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol is investigating the death of a 47-year-old San 
Diego County resident who was killed Friday in an apparent traffic accident on 
a rural road near the Riverside County line. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Felipe Estrella Gonzalez, who lived in the small 
community of Rainbow, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
No one else was hurt in the incident, which involved only the victim's vehicle, 
the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
Estrella was driving a pickup south on Rainbow Valley Boulevard at about 50 
m.p.h. at 7 p.m., authorities said, when he lost control, ran off the road and 
ended up in a drainage ditch. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics tried to revive Estrella, but he was declared dead at the scene at 
8:18 p.m., according to the county medical examiner's office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
